Use P_iron_FLUX_in (Particulate iron into cell)
  mmol/m^3 cm/s
convert cm to m by multiplying 1 m/100 cm
  mmol/m^3 m/s = mmol/m^2/s

1) compute net flux thru the laters 
  F_"net" =F_"top" - F_"bottom" 
  
2) estimate the layer inventory
  Σ_"layer" =C_"layer" * Δz
    C_"layer" = 1 mmol/m^3
    Δz = m
    Σ_"layer" =  mmol/m^2

3) define the inverse time operator
  λ_"layer" = F_"net" / Σ_"layer"  
  λ_"layer" = 1/sec

4) write to new diagnostics to subtract from DOC & DOCr
DOC_scav= λ_"layer" * DOC_loc
DOCr_scav= λ_"layer" * DOCr_loc

DOC = ....-DOC_scav
DOCr= ....-DOCr_scav

do this in marbl_interior_tendency_mod.F90


  later on
    multiply by 0.01 and stick it in a kmt conditional
